rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor resource for codelist C85839

self.title: CDISC SDTM Pharmacokinetic Parameter Terminology by Code

definition: Parameter codes used to describe the time-concentration curve.
name: PK Parameters Code
preferredTerm: CDISC SDTM Pharmacokinetic Parameter Terminology by Code
synonyms: PK Parameters Code

terms.definition: Predicted accumulation ratio for area under the curve (AUC) calculated using the Lambda z estimated from single dose data.
terms.preferredTerm: Accumulation Index using Lambda z
synonyms: Accumulation Index using Lambda z

terms.definition: The area under the curve (AUCTAU) at steady state divided by the area under the curve over the initial dosing interval.

terms.definition: The maximum concentration at steady state divided by the maximum concentration during the initial dosing interval.

terms.definition: The minimum concentration at steady state divided by the minimum concentration during the initial dosing interval.

terms.definition: The trough concentration at steady state divided by the trough concentration during the initial dosing interval.

terms.definition: The area under the curve (AUC) from the time of dosing to the time of the last observation, regardless of whether the last concentration is measurable or not.
